[[2026-04-13 22:16:28]] {Bash: git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
PoC Step 9: Configurable vector store with Protocol-based abstraction

Builds contextualized, metadata-tagged chunks from parsed requirement
trees and stores them in a vector store for targeted retrieval.
All settings (embedding model, vector DB backend, distance metric,
chunk format) are configurable via JSON config or CLI flags.

- EmbeddingProvider Protocol + SentenceTransformerEmbedder implementation
- VectorStoreProvider Protocol + ChromaDB persistent store implementation
- VectorStoreConfig dataclass (JSON-serializable, all tuneable params)
- ChunkBuilder: TDD 5.9 format with MNO/release header, hierarchy path,
  req ID, body text, tables as Markdown, image captions
- VectorStoreBuilder: orchestration with chunk deduplication
- CLI: --config, --model, --metric, --rebuild, --info, --query
- 57 tests (config, protocols, chunks, dedup, builder, integration)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
EOF
)" }
