PoC Step 10: Query pipeline with 6-stage architecture

Implements the full query pipeline from TDD section 7:
- Stage 1: Query analysis (keyword-based mock + LLM-driven with fallback)
- Stage 2: MNO/Release resolution from graph node discovery
- Stage 3: Graph scoping with entity/feature/plan/title lookup + BFS traversal
- Stage 4: Targeted RAG retrieval with scoped and metadata strategies + diversity
- Stage 5: Context assembly with graph enrichment (hierarchy, standards, cross-refs)
- Stage 6: LLM synthesis with citation extraction (mock returns structured summary)

All stages have mock implementations enabling full pipeline testing without API keys.
55 new tests (342 total), all passing.

